                "Content": "<color=#37FFFF>Paimon: </color>Sumpter Beasts are adorable! Paimon likes how the people who keep them give them each a special name based on their most distinctive traits!<br><color=#37FFFF>Traveler: </color>For all we know, the Sumpter Beasts might be giving each of us a name in return. Maybe that's how they respond when we call their name.<br><color=#37FFFF>Paimon: </color>Really? So what kind of name do think they'd give us?<br><color=#37FFFF>Traveler: </color>(Sumpter Beast noises)<br><color=#37FFFF>Paimon: </color>How is anyone supposed to understand that!<br><color=#37FFFF>Traveler: </color>A rough translation would be...<br><color=#37FFFF>Traveler: </color>\"Vociferous Pestiferous Melliculus Niveous Micro-Bipedal.\"<br><color=#37FFFF>Traveler: </color>That's the scientific name, of course.<br><color=#37FFFF>Paimon: </color>Oh? What would the common name be then?<br><color=#37FFFF>Traveler: </color>\"Noisy Two-Legged Critter\"<br><color=#37FFFF>Paimon: </color>Hey! Why keep only the negative traits?",
